c.	The Property Officer to maintain property cards to facilitate the physical count of PPE items. Determine the officials/employees to whom the equipment were issued and issue the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) to pinpoint the direct person responsible thereof. Moreover, renew all ARE every three years to update the information of the end-user of the equipment listed in the RPCPPE;

d.	The Property Officer to prepare the IIRUP for all unserviceable property so that they may be properly disposed of and derecognized from the books of accounts; and





e.	The Municipal Assessor to secure the necessary documents to support the ownership claims of the Municipality over the purchased land.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
create a team/committee to conduct an immediate physical count of all its property, plant and equipment. They are required to submit the RPCPPE on or before January 31 of each year, copy furnished the COA Auditor concerned pursuant to Section 266 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I;
require the committee to check the conditions of all LGU properties. Any damage, obsolete and unserviceable property shall be reported in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report and immediately request for disposal, if any. Lastly, the inventory reports should be reconciled with the accounting records to determine the correctness of the property records;
require each Department Head to conduct every year a physical inventory count of all properties under their office and to submit inventory report to the inventory committee for the random validation of the existence of the property; and
require both the Accountant and General Services Office to maintain and update records and ledgers of all properties owned by the LGU pursuant to Section 269, Volume I of GAM for LGUs.

We recommended that the procuring entity strictly adhere to the pertinent provisions of the 2016 Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations to ensure transparency and accountability in the procurement process. We specifically recommended that Management instruct:

The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) comply with the submission of the Final APP to the GPPB on or before the end of January of the budget year and it shall be posted in the GPPB Website to ensure transparency in the procurement process and in the implementation of procurement contracts;
