observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management dispose the unserviceable properties of the agency in accordance with Sections 76 and 79 of PD 1445. Disposal thereof may:
1. generate additional funds, when sold, to be used for the agency’s operations;
2. relieve the responsible official of accountability over said properties;
3. prevent said unserviceable properties from further deterioration and loss of value; and
4. allow the agency to use the space being occupied by these unserviceable properties.

In order to correct the aforementioned deficiencies, we recommended the following:
Conduct the required annual physical count of the PPE as of December 31 of every year.  The actual count may be undertaken any month during the current year, but has to be updated at year-end.
To ensure the success of the inventory taking, all heads of offices are advised to instruct their staff to cooperate in the conduct of physical count;
Invite a representative of the Auditor to witness the inventory taking;
Require the reconciliation of Property and Accounting records after the physical count and effect the necessary adjustments, if any ;
Require the submission of the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment to the Property Unit and the COA office for verification and reconciliation of the results of physical count with the complete PPELC and PCs maintained by the Accounting Office and the Property Unit respectively;
Require the  Property Unit and the Accounting Office to maintain  complete, accurate  and up-dated Property Cards (PCs) and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card (PPELC), respectively;
Require the Municipal Treasurer who is also the property custodian to file the AREs  of all movable non expendable properties and cause the renewal of the same  every January of the 3rd year after issue  in order to facilitate the physical count of PPE and to easily identify the official/employee responsible in case of loss;
Require the posting of property tag/number on the prominent portion of every movable non expendable property/equipment, and
Proper disposal of unserviceable property be made.

Require the WATSAN council to prepare a reasonable work plan for the  consideration of the Sangguniang Bayan in the provision of annual funding;
Either assist the community to  establish the WSPs through capacity building activities for eventual turn-over or undertake ring-fencing; and
Monitor and Evaluate the physical and financial aspects of operations  including its functionality, effectiveness and efficiency for the benefit of the intended end-users.

